or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">There was=
 a little though</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The false post on the SEC=E2=80=99=
s X account was up for a number of minutes before the agency clarified that=
 it was inaccurate. In that period, Bitcoin posted a relatively modest jump=
 to almost $48,000 from about $46,700 before falling back toward $45,000.</=
p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Eh? If you bought Bitcoin at=C2=A0$48,000 upon=
 seeing that tweet, and then sold it at $45,000 after realizing that the tw=
eet was fake, I would love to hear from you. Why? Why not just wait? If you=
 think=C2=A0Bitcoin is worth $48,000 when the SEC approves spot Bitcoin ETF=
s, then =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I mean =E2=80=A6=C2=A0the tweet was fake, but if the=
 contents of the tweet turn out to be true=C2=A0<em>today</em>, won=E2=80=
=99t you regret selling yesterday?<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#foot=
note-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !=
important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;=
">
<span>[1]</span>
