uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMTAvc2VjLXMtY29tcHJvbWlzZWQtYWNjb3VudC1hbXBsaW=
ZpZXMteC10cnVzdC1zZWN1cml0eS1jb25jZXJucz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMTEwMjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGR=
iZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDAxMTAm=
dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7e1d3da8" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  as a business matter</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The high-profile breach comes at a time when X=
 and billionaire owner Elon Musk are seeking to win back trust from both us=
ers and advertisers, many of which have been dismayed by Musk=E2=80=99s fre=
e-for-all style of leadership since his 2022 takeover. Musk has pivoted awa=
y from some of the prior regime=E2=80=99s efforts to rein in offensive or h=
armful content, and has severely scaled back staff to save on costs. Those =
cuts have led to regular bugs and outages.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThis has to be the most sophisticated=
 use of a stolen Twitter account ever,=E2=80=9D said Alex Stamos, chief tru=
st officer at SentinelOne and former security chief at Meta Platforms Inc. =
=E2=80=9CAt a minimum, this indicates that the hollowed-out X team can=E2=
=80=99t keep up with advances in account takeover techniques.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But it=E2=80=99s definitely a point for Musk i=
n his long dumb game of trolling the SEC.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To be clear, I am not saying it is=C2=A0<em>li=
kely=C2=A0</em>that Elon Musk, who controls Twitter, took over the SEC=E2=
=80=99s account in order to tweet a fake announcement to troll the SEC. I t=
hink the likelihood of that is close to zero. I am just saying that it woul=
d be the absolute funniest Money Stuff story of all time. Just all of my in=
terests, right there.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another irony: I like to say around here that =
=E2=80=9Ceverything is securities fraud,=E2=80=9D and so of course when thi=
s story came out people emailed me to say =E2=80=9Cis this securities fraud=
 yuk yuk yuk.=E2=80=9D But: no? I mean, nothing here is legal advice, and e=
verything is securities fraud, but let=E2=80=99s say that someone hacked th=
e SEC to manipulate the price of Bitcoin. Bitcoin is not a security? The SE=
C <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33957045.258408/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMDcvd2h=
lbi1pcy1hLXRva2VuLW5vdC1hLXNlY3VyaXR5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMTAyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJn=
V0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDExMCZ1d=
G1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB87fca7ad" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  thinks that almost every crypto asset is a security</a>, but it really do=
es make a single explicit exception for Bitcoin.<a class=3D"footnote-index"=
 href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display:=
 inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a> So if the SEC figures out who hacked its Twitter account, and if it fi=
gures out that that person did it to make a quick profit on Bitcoin by mani=
pulating the market and deceiving investors, that=E2=80=99s still not secur=
ities fraud. It=E2=80=99s regular fraud, it=E2=80=99s wire fraud, maybe it=
=E2=80=99s commodities fraud, but whatever it is is not under the SEC=E2=80=
=99s jurisdiction. The SEC =E2=80=9Csaid that it would work with law enforc=
ement to investigate the incident,=E2=80=9D but it has no power=C2=A0<em>it=
self=C2=A0</em>to bring charges against anyone for manipulating Bitcoin.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still, there are securities that are tied to t=
he price of Bitcoin, and whose prices would be influenced by news about Bit=
coin ETFs, and which were arguably manipulated by this fake tweet. The most=
 obvious examples would be =C2=A0=E2=80=A6 spot Bitcoin ETFs? Those don=E2=
=80=99t trade yet. Because the SEC hasn=E2=80=99t approved them. So the fak=
e tweet couldn=E2=80=99t have manipulated them. But Bitcoin=C2=A0<em>future=
s=C2=A0</em>ETFs=C2=A0<em>do=C2=A0</em>trade, as does the Grayscale Bitcoin=
 Trust (GBTC), a pot of Bitcoins that hopes to convert into an ETF. I suppo=
se you could have manipulated their prices with this tweet. The tweet went =
out after 4 p.m. so the stock market was closed, but the price of the ProSh=
ares Bitcoin Strategy ETF did in fact bounce around a bit in after-hours tr=
ading yesterday; it closed at $22.72 and spiked as high as $23.50 at 4:12 p=
.m., after the tweet. So, sure, securities fraud, fine.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway, the great counter-troll here would be =
for the SEC to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/339=
57045.258408/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9maW5hbmNlL3JlZ3VsYXRpb24vc2Vjcy1kZW=
Npc2lvbi1vbi1zcG90LWJpdGNvaW4tZXRmcy1jb3VsZC1nby1hLWZldy1kaWZmZXJlbnQtd2F5c=
y05NmQ3NjU4OT9tb2Q9aXRwX3dzag/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB83186d1f" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 announce today</a> =E2=80=9Cyou know what, all the Bitcoin ETF application=
s are rejected, we=E2=80=99ll see you in court again. We <em>were=C2=A0</em=
>going to approve them, but it turns out that the Bitcoin market is still t=
oo vulnerable to manipulation, as you can tell by the fact that someone hac=
ked our Twitter to manipulate Bitcoin.=E2=80=9D</p>
