ce it converts into an ETF, which is less than the current 2%, but still wa=
y more than the 0.3% that BlackRock plans to charge. I wrote:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are the first person to offer =E2=80=9C=
Bitcoins in a pot=E2=80=9D as a product, you can charge a huge premium.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But eventually, like, BlackRock will catch up,=
 and then you probably can=E2=80=99t.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A reader emailed to point out that this isn=E2=
=80=99t necessarily the whole story. If you are the first person to offer =
