em.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is good for you, generally, but it is a t=
ax problem: If you=C2=A0<em>sell=C2=A0</em>your GBTC shares, you=E2=80=99ll=
 have a big gain and have to pay taxes on it. If you just keep those shares=
, you don=E2=80=99t pay taxes (yet). That is a reason not to sell.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Soon, probably, you will have your choice of B=
itcoin ETFs. They will all be about the same, and you might prefer to buy o=
ne with 0.2% fees rather than one with 1.5% fees. But if you=C2=A0<em>alrea=
dy own=C2=A0</em>shares in Grayscale=E2=80=99s Bitcoin trust when it conver=
ts to an ETF, the math isn=E2=80=99t so simple. If you=C2=A0<em>sell=C2=A0<=
/em>the Grayscale ETF and=C2=A0<em>buy=C2=A0</em>a cheap one, you will save=
 on annual fees =E2=80=94=C2=A0but you=E2=80=99ll probably pay a lot of tax=
es on your gains.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"=
